ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Good intro ir course. Would recommend

This is a survey course of the major theoretical and methodological approaches within the International Relations field. I would recommend it to anyone interested in getting a better sense of the IR field. It is an introductory course that can serve as a foundation for more in-depth study of otherfields such as security studies, civil wars, diplomacy, etc.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Good review and grad level reinforcement
This course helped me tie all the different research strands within the field together, providing a larger picture of the various theoretical and methodological approaches.
